<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="form-n">form <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /fɔːm/    美 /fɔːrm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c">1.★ <strong>[C] 形状；外形；体型：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My garden is <strong>in the form of</strong> a square.
我的花园是方形的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The human form has changed little over the last 30,000 years.
3万多年以来，人类的体形没有多大变化。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c-u">2.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 形式；形态：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Ice and snow are <strong>forms of</strong> water.
冰和雪是水的不同形态。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This disease often <strong>takes the form of</strong> high fever
这种疾病常以高烧的症状出现。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Nowadays the beggars appreciate our help <strong>in the form of</strong> money rather than food.
如今的乞讨者喜欢我们用钱而不是食物来帮他们。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-c">3.★ <strong>[C] 类型；种类：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bicycle is an environment-friendly <strong>form of</strong> transport.
自行车是一种环保的交通工具。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Poets use many different <strong>forms of</strong> poetry to express themselves.
诗人们用许多种诗歌形式来抒情达意。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="4-c">4.★ <strong>[C] 表格；格式：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>fill in / out a form 填写表格</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="5c">5.<strong>[C] [语法] 形式；词形：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The continuous form of “stand” is “standing”.
stand的进行式是standing。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Complete the sentences with the correct form of the verbs.
用动词的正确形式完成句子。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>You'd sound a lot more polite if you make a request <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (以…形式) a question.  （2009 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. in the form of  </p></div>